I'm getting the error below if I set this property to `AxisDirection.left` or `AxisDirection.right`:

```dart
======== Exception caught by gesture ===============================================================
The following assertion was thrown while handling a gesture:
'package:flutter/src/widgets/overscroll_indicator.dart': Failed assertion: line 736 pos 14: 'notification.metrics.axis == widget.axis': is not true.
```

The code is (the listView uses `scrollDirection: Axis.vertical` by default):

```dart
StretchingOverscrollIndicator(
        axisDirection: AxisDirection.right,
        child: ListView.builder(
          itemCount: 200,
          itemBuilder: (context, index) {
            return Padding(
              padding: const EdgeInsets.all(8.0),
              child: Text('${index * 1000}'),
            );
          },
        ),
      )
```

From my understanding, this should match the axis/scrollDirection of the inner scrollable widget, I believe this is woth documenting :)

